abstract: <jats:p>High–cycle multiaxial fatigue tests under proportional and non-proportional loading conditions with various combinations of superimposed static mean stresses was carried out on Cu-ETP copper. The results show differences in fatigue life between various ratios of mean stresses. These results are similar to others described in the literature.</jats:p>
title: The Influence of Multiaxial Superimposed Static Mean Stress on High-Cycle Fatigue Life of Cu-ETP Copper
